The paper deals with the problem of sequencing a set of closely related DNA molecules, which is a problem in bioinformatics. However, the paper approaches the problem from an information theoretic point of view, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic models and denoising methods, which are common in machine learning and data science (cs.DS, cs.DM). The paper also addresses the issue of error probabilities, which is a topic in statistics and probability theory (cs.LG). Finally, the paper is specifically focused on the problem of pooled-DNA sequencing, which is a subfield of bioinformatics, suggesting that cs.BIO may also be a relevant sub-category.
